{{see|Aubergine}}
==English==
[[Image:Aubergine.jpg|thumb|right|200px|an aubergine]]
===Etymology===
French, from Catalan albergínia, from Arabic al-bādhinjān the eggplant, ultimately from Middle Indo-Aryan *vātiñjaṇa-, vātiṅgaṇa-

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# an [[Asian]] [[plant]], ''[[Solanum melongena]]'', [[cultivate]]d for its [[edible]] [[purple]], [[green]], or [[white]] [[ovoid]] [[fruit]]
# the fruit of this plant, eaten as a [[vegetable]]
# a dark purple [[colour]]

===Synonyms===
*{{italbrac-colon|plant}} [[brinjal]], [[eggplant]] {{italbrac|US|Australia}}
*{{italbrac-colon|fruit}} [[eggplant]] {{italbrac|US|Australia}}
